cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for detecting errors in pre-trained visual classifiers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training a binary classifier, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of natural image transformations and the analysis of invariance in decision-making suggest the involvement of artificial intelligence techniques, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves experiments with multiple data sets, which suggests the involvement of neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the detection of novelty, which suggests the involvement of cryptography and security, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
